The coordinates of $E$ are $(4,4)$, so $OE=4\sqrt{2}$. The area of $OEC$ is thus \[\frac{1}{2}(OE)(EC)=\frac{1}{2}(4\sqrt{2})(2)=\boxed{4\sqrt{2}}.\]

We first find the $y$-intercept of the second line.  Since the line passes through $(8,0),$ its $y$-intercept is $(0,-4).$

[asy]
draw((0,-1)--(0,13));
draw((-1,0)--(10,0));
fill((0,0)--(0,8)--(8,0)--cycle,gray);
fill((0,0)--(0,12)--(6,0)--cycle,gray);
