Let $F$ be the foot of the perpendicular from $D$ to line $OC.$  Then $OF = 8 - CF.$  Also, $\triangle ECF \sim \triangle EOB,$ so
\[\frac{OF}{8} = \frac{4}{12},\]which implies $OF = \frac{2}{3}.$  Therefore, $CF = 8 - OF = \frac{22}{3}.$

Then the area of quadrilateral $OBEC$ is
