draw((0,5)--(0,0)--(15,0)--(15,5),linewidth(1));
draw((0,5)--(2,2)--(5,5)--(12,-2)--(15,5),linewidth(.7));
label("A",(0,5),N);
draw("B",(5,5),N);
draw("C",(15,5),N);
draw("$x^{\circ}$",(2.5,2.5),N);
draw("$y^{\circ}$",(12,-2),N);
draw((0,.5)--(.5,.5)--(.5,0),linewidth(.7));
draw((15,.5)--(14.5,.5)--(14.5,0),linewidth(.7));

[/asy]

Since $\overline{AB}$ and $\overline{BC}$ are opposite rays, $\angle A + \angle B + \angle C = 180^\circ,$ so $\angle B = 78^\circ.$  Then $x + y = 180^\circ - 28^\circ - 78^\circ - 26^\circ = \boxed{48^\circ}.$
